        parameters - a map of the parameters to apply to the query

      • update

        int update(String query,
           Map<Integer,Object> parameters)
    throws SQLException
        Executes the specified SQL query after applying the specified parameters, and returns the integer returned in case of an update.
        Parameters:
        query - the SQL query to prepare and then execute
        parameters - a map of the parameters to apply to the query
        Returns:
        either (1) the row count for SQL Data Manipulation Language (DML) statements or (2) 0 for SQL statements that return nothing
        Throws:
        SQLException - if a database access error occurs
        See Also:
        PreparedStatement.executeUpdate()
